# mongo-sts-with-nfs

1.Configure NFS server in local machine
2.Create all kubernetes resources
3.Run the following commands to get the exact FQDN
  >)kubectl run cnt -i --tty --image=busybox --rm
  >)nslookup <headless-service-name>
4.From client pod(which created using <pod.yaml> file) connect to any 
  stateful pod using the result returned by the previous command
  >)mongo mongodb://<username>:<password>@<target-pod-ip>.<headless-svc-name>.default.svc.cluster.local

